---

#### **FPIC & UNDRIP Violations**
This was a **textbook FPIC failure**:
- **Not Free**: Police used rubber bullets, water cannons in freezing weather, tear gas — 700+ arrests.<grok:render card_id="e5842b" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">1</argument>
</grok:render><grok:render card_id="14276f" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">7</argument>
</grok:render>
- **Not Prior**: Army Corps contacted tribe 12 times but didn't do full cultural survey.<grok:render card_id="3a9395" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">6</argument>
</grok:render>
- **Not Informed**: Environmental review missed sacred sites and spill risks.
- **No Consent**: Tribe's 2016 resolution said **NO** — ignored.

**UNDRIP Ties**:
- **Art. 19 (Consent)**: Tribe excluded from planning.<grok:render card_id="3b8c5d" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">1</argument>
</grok:render>
- **Art. 25–32 (Lands)**: Violated treaty lands.
- **UN Expert (2016)**: Called it a "human rights violation."<grok:render card_id="c061d4" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">1</argument>
</grok:render>

---

#### **What Happened to the Project?**
- **Pipeline Runs**: Operational since 2017, carrying oil.
- **Tribe Wins**: 2020 court order for new review; 2021 shutdown threat (later lifted).
- **Ongoing**: 2023–2025: Biden admin re-evaluates; tribe pushes for reroute. No major spills yet, but risks remain.

---

#### **Impact & Legacy**
- **Global Movement**: Inspired **#NoDAPL** — 87 tribes supported; celebs (Leonardo DiCaprio) joined.<grok:render card_id="ad1d70" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">1</argument>
</grok:render>
- **Environmental**: Highlighted fossil fuels' risks; boosted renewable energy talks.
- **For Tribes**: Proved **UNDRIP works in courts** — led to Canada's 2021 UNDRIP law.<grok:render card_id="85e0f9" card_type="citation_card" type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">0</argument>
</grok:render>
- **Cost to Company**: $1.5B+ in delays, reroutes.

---

**One Sentence**:  
Standing Rock showed **UNDRIP + FPIC in action** — a tribe’s NO sparked a world movement, slowing a pipeline and changing laws.

**Ties to FPT/SSC**: FPT’s **glyph logs** could’ve proven the violation early, forcing a real YES/NO vote.

